  .section.s2(data-destination="core")
    a(name="core")
    .row
      .medium-12.columns.intro
        .quote "Data is the new oil" - Neelie Kroes (2012).
        h3 We build next-gen data applications. Data is valuable, but if unrefined it cannot be used. Orikami helps organisations exploiting their data.

    .row
      .medium-4.columns
        img.svg(src="images/curiosity.svg")
        h4.green Curious
        p Orikami stimulates curiosity. We know how to ask the right questions and explore data.
        p That's how we uncover the most fascinating and rewarding stories.
        p The stories that we fold into products.

      .medium-4.columns
        img.svg(src="images/analytical.svg")
        h4.orange Analytic
        p Data always has its secrets. Our data scientists are fully equipped with modern tools and mathematics.
        p We are ready to reveal and build. Enriching data by coupling open datasets and api's? No problem!
        p Cluster analysis on noisy data? Cool!

      .medium-4.columns
        img.svg.last(src="images/together.svg")
        h4.red Together
        p At orikami we collaborate. We partner up. We co-create.
        p We have the technical know-how to develop next-gen data applications.
        p We need you for knowledge about the problem domain. Together, we are an unbeatable team!

  .section.parallax.s5(data-destination="data-science")
    a(name="data-science")
    .row
      .small-12.columns
        h2 Excellence in data science

  .section.s6
    .row
      .small-12.columns
        h3 Orikami is not your run-of-the-mill data science company. We are not statisticians. We are computational neuroscientists. We are artificial intelligence scientists. We are real data scientists.
    .row
      .medium-8.columns.small-10.columns.small-centered
        object.fill.venn(type="image/svg+xml" data="images/venn.svg")
    .row
      .medium-4.columns
        h4 Hacking Skills
        p Data is a commodity traded electronically, therefore, we need to speak hacker. Far from 'black hat' activities, data hackers must be able to manipulate text files at the command-line, thinking algorithmically, and be interested in learning new tools.
      .medium-4.columns
        h4 Math & Statistics
        p Once we have acquired and cleaned the data, the next step is to actually extract insight from it. We need to apply appropriate math and statistics methods, which requires familiarity with these tools.
      .medium-4.columns
        h4 Domain Expertise
        p Science is about discovery and building knowledge, which requires motivating questions about the world and hypotheses that can be brought to data and tested with statistical methods. Domain relevant questions first, then data.


